Hi,
On Fri, 19 Mar 1999 13:18:13 -0800 (PST), Dan Hollis
<goemon@sasami.anime.net> said:
> On Fri, 19 Mar 1999, Stephen C. Tweedie wrote:
>> Frankly, Unix has really never supported disk IO stream bandwidth
>> reservation.
> IRIX does.
Only on certain volumes, only if you use a specific, non-Unix API, and
only if you allocate the file in advance with the requested bandwidth.
The standard Unix API does _not_ make any bandwidth guarantees.
--Stephen
